{
  "text": "The original aim of the research presented in this paper was to extend the results of [CITATION_1] to fields of characteristic 2. As in the course of this work some proofs of [CITATION_2] were revised, we decided, in this paper, to present a full classification of 6-dimensional nilpotent Lie algebras that is valid over all fields. In addition, some results in [CITATION_3] relied on computer calculations (specifically, computing a Gr\u00f6bner bases for ideals in a polynomial rings), while the arguments of the present paper are all theoretical with no computer calculations involved. Nevertheless, we should mention here that several of the theoretical arguments in Section 5 were inspired by Gr\u00f6bner basis computations in the computational algebra system Magma [CITATION_4] and it would have been significantly more difficult, maybe even impossible, to obtain the classification in Theorem 1.1 without performing such computations.",
  "citation_candidates": [
